column5: Travel remained great from IBR, Lots of cars and trucks out today. Fishing was all so great, lots of whities and 1 laker. Fished 85' with tubes and spoons. Had to keep the laker (don't like keeping them that big) as she inhaled the spoon while reeling it up causing too much damage to send her back down ! Little guy sure got a kick out of it though Good luck this weekend and stay dry!
VERY nice.. food for the table, not much you can do sometimes and it's all part of the game.
Now there's a nice looking laker Congrats Jasper on the enormous brute
Awesome! Nice fish  Just hoping to get out on Simcoe this weekend for at least 1 decent laker before the season closes.
